Durban - A man in his 60’s died on Monday morning after a diving incident at Warner Beach along the south coast of KwaZulu-Natal. “ER24 arrived at the beach at 9am and were informed that a diving boat was bringing a patient to the beach. After a short time, a boat arrived on the beach. A male, believed to be in his 60's, was found lying inside, motionless,” said Russel Meiring, ER24 spokesperson. Meiring said paramedics and lifeguards assessed the man and found that he showed no signs of life. CPR and advanced life support interventions were immediately initiated in an effort to revive the man. “Unfortunately, after some time, no vital signs returned and the man was pronounced dead,” said Meiring. He said details surrounding the incident are unknown but police were on scene and are investigating. In another incident, the National Sea Rescue Institute said they are still searching for a 23-year-old diver who went missing in the Port of Durban on Sunday. Daily News